==Galician==
[[File:Lalín, Casa do Patrón 03-02c.jpg|thumb|Galician ''xugos'' ("yokes")]]
[[File:Museo Liste, xugos para o gando.JPG |thumb|A parir of Galician ''xugos de molida'' ("head yokes")]]
===Etymology===
Attested since the 13th century ({{m|gl||jugo}}). From Old Galician and {{inh|gl|roa-opt|-}}, from {{inh|gl|la|jugum}}, {{m|la|iugum}}. Compare {{cog|pt|jugo}}, {{cog|es|yugo}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|gl|[ˈʃuɣʊ]}}
===Noun===
{{gl-noun|m}}
# [[yoke]]
#: {{syn|gl|canga}}
# chain or strap that connects both parts of a [[flail]]
#: {{syn|gl|cedoiro|entrecarto|inzadoiro|loro|pealla}}
====Derived terms====
* {{l|gl|xugo de cancís|t=withers yoke}}
* {{l|gl|xugo de canga|t=bow yoke}}
* {{l|gl|xugo de mulida|t=head yoke}}
====Related terms====
* {{l|gl|xunguir}}
